name: basic
text: What are you still doing here,  Jolie?

name: basic
text: Go find your grampa and get to work!

name: basic
text: Oh no!

name: basic
text: undefined

name: basic
text: What happened here?!

name: basic
text: I don't know!

name: basic
text: I got here and the whole place was a mess!

name: basic
text: Can you help me tidy up?

name: basic
text: Teddy's scarf! Somebody must've taken him!

name: basic
text: Try not to panic, Jo.

name: basic
text: Maybe he just got scared and ran off.

name: basic
text: But he never goes anywhere without his scarf!

name: basic
text: I think he's in trouble!

name: basic
text: Is this your coffee, Gramps?

name: basic
text: Nope, that's from Bean Town. I only drink Holdgers!

name: basic
text: Who could've done this?

name: basic
text: It must've been Wells.

name: basic
text: He's always trying to get you in trouble, and he doesn't like animals!

name: basic
text: Slow down, Jo.

name: basic
text: But what if Wells kidnapped Teddy?

name: basic
text: Then we need evidence.

name: basic
text: You're right, Gramps. Let's investigate!

name: basic
text: I'm afraid my papers have gone missing in this mess.

name: basic
text: You'll have to get started without me.

name: basic
text: Okay. I'll find Teddy!

name: basic
text: And I'll figure out the shirt, too.

name: basic
text: I knew I could count on you, Jo!

name: basic
text: Why don't you go upstairs and see the archivist?

name: basic
text: He's our expert record keeper.

name: basic
text: I need your help!

name: basic
text: Who are you?

name: basic
text: I'm Leopold's grandkid!

name: basic
text: Sorry, I'm too busy for kids right now.

name: basic
text: Now if only I could read this thing.

name: basic
text: Can't believe I lost my reading glasses.

name: basic
text: I bet the archivist could use this!

name: basic
text: Ah, that's better!

name: basic
text: Did you have a question?

name: basic
text: Yes! I was wondering-

name: basic
text: Wait a minute!

name: basic
text: Where did you get that coffee?

name: basic
text: Oh, that's from Bean Town.

name: basic
text: I ran into Wells there this morning.

name: basic
text: Wells? I knew it!

name: basic
text: Do you know anything about this slip?

name: basic
text: I found it on an old shirt.

name: basic
text: An old shirt? Try the university.

name: basic
text: You can talk to a textile expert there.

name: basic
text: What's a textile expert?

name: basic
text: They study clothes and fabric.

name: basic
text: Great! Thanks for the help!

name: basic
text: Head over to the university.

name: basic
text: You can talk to a textile expert there.

name: basic
text: Hello there!

name: basic
text: Wow! What is all this stuff?

name: basic
text: It's our Norwegian Craft exhibit!

name: basic
text: Can I give you the tour?

name: basic
text: Sorry, I'm in a hurry.

name: basic
text: Do you know what this slip is?

name: basic
text: Looks like a dry cleaning receipt.

name: basic
text: Thanks.

name: basic
text: Now I Just need to find all the cleaners from way back in 1916.

name: basic
text: Maybe I can help!

name: basic
text: I've got a stack of business cards from my favorite cleaners.

name: basic
text: Why don't you take a look?

name: basic
text: This place was around in 1916! I can start there!

name: basic
text: You haven't seen any badgers around here, have you?

name: basic
text: Badgers? No.

name: basic
text: Okay. Thanks anyway.

name: basic
text: Hi! How can I help you?

name: basic
text: I need to find the owner of this slip.

name: basic
text: Well, I can't show our log books to just anybody.

name: basic
text: Please?

name: basic
text: It's for Grampa Leo. He's a historian!

name: basic
text: Leo... you mean Leopold?

name: basic
text: Your gramps is awesome! Always full of stories.

name: basic
text: Guess it couldn't hurt to let you take a look.

name: basic
text: Here's the log book.

name: basic
text: It's a match!

name: basic
text: Theodora Youmans must be the owner!

name: basic
text: Do you know who Theodora Youmans is?

name: basic
text: Hmmm... not sure. Why don't you try the library?

name: basic
text: Thanks for the help!

name: basic
text: Oh, hello there!

name: basic
text: How can I help you?

name: basic
text: Have you seen a badger around here?

name: basic
text: I'm afraid not.

name: basic
text: Please let me know if you do.

name: basic
text: I'm also looking for Theodora Youmans. Have you heard of her?

name: basic
text: Theodora Youmans? Of course!

name: basic
text: Check out our microfiche. It's right through that door.

name: basic
text: Youmans was a suffragist!

name: basic
text: She helped get votes for women!

name: basic
text: Wells! What was he doing here? I should ask the librarian.

name: basic
text: What was Wells doing here?

name: basic
text: He was looking for a taxidermist.

name: basic
text: What's a taxidermist?

name: basic
text: Not sure. Here, let me look it up.

name: basic
text: \Taxidermy: the art of preparing, stuffing, and mounting the skins of animals.\

name: basic
text: Oh no... Teddy!

name: basic
text: Can you help me find Wells?

name: basic
text: You could ask the archivist. He knows everybody!

name: basic
text: Jolie! I was hoping you'd stop by. Any news on the shirt artifact?

name: basic
text: I haven't quite figured it out just yet...

name: basic
text: Well, get on it. I'm counting on you and your gramps to figure this out!

name: basic
text: Can you help me? I need to find Wells!

name: basic
text: I haven't seen him.

name: basic
text: Please? This is really important.

name: basic
text: Sorry, can't help you.

name: basic
text: Okay. Thanks anyway.

name: basic
text: Do you have any info on Theodora Youmans?

name: basic
text: Theodora Youmans? Is that who owned the shirt?

name: basic
text: Yep.

name: basic
text: Why didn't you say so?

name: basic
text: Youmans was a suffragist here in Wisconsin.

name: basic
text: She led marches and helped women get the right to vote!

name: basic
text: Wait a sec. Women couldn't vote?!

name: basic
text: Nope. But Youmans and other suffragists worked hard to change that.

name: basic
text: Thanks to them, Wisconsin was the first state to approve votes for women!

name: basic
text: Wow!

name: basic
text: Here's a call number to find more info in the Stacks.

name: basic
text: Where are the Stacks?

name: basic
text: Right outside the door.

name: basic
text: Hey, this is Youmans!

name: basic
text: And look! She's wearing the shirt!

name: basic
text: I should go to the Capitol and tell everyone!
